After installing nginx on ec2 - sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default
server{} content is added there.

server {
    listen 80;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }
}

KEY - SSH

ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "github-actions" on my wsl machine
~/.ssh/id_rsa        ← private key (GOES TO GITHUB) - the key we added in secrets area - Now GitHub can SSH into EC2 using that key
~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub    ← public key (GOES TO EC2) - this should go to nano ~/.ssh/authorized_keys on ec2
